{
  "texts": [
    "Also, for image models, a recent study has demonstrated that adding a standard level of random noise into the gradient update might not always work well to prevent gradient leakage attacks on medical images [52].",
    "Recently, an open language model (OLMo) has been introduced to provide open access to the data, code, and model [242].",
    "The main purpose of OLMo is to facilitate open research on language models.",
    "They performed PII filtering to remove it from the data, and they also provided a tool to remove PII data upon request.",
    "Though it followed existing practices to obscure the PII exposure and identify and remove toxic content, it did not explicitly discuss the impacts of various attacks outlined in this survey paper and how to mitigate those risks."
  ]
}